253
00:19:20,430 --> 00:19:23,780
So you'll hand over your child to a one-day
nanny from online in the evening?

254
00:19:23,780 --> 00:19:25,210
You won't let your child stay at the nursery?

255
00:19:25,210 --> 00:19:26,340
Right.

256
00:19:26,500 --> 00:19:28,780
Goodness. Since my mother is far away from us,

257
00:19:28,780 --> 00:19:31,690
and my child got sick,
things were hectic for me.

258
00:19:31,940 --> 00:19:35,050
My mother-in-law has
to take care of my child without rest,

259
00:19:35,050 --> 00:19:37,430
but my husband is just
watching her from the other side.

260
00:19:37,430 --> 00:19:39,630
You can apply for leave in this way.

261
00:19:39,630 --> 00:19:42,620
Gosh. Anyways, I haven't seen him do anything nice.

262
00:19:43,030 --> 00:19:45,920
So you're not yet willing
to have another child, right?

263
00:19:46,410 --> 00:19:48,180
My mother-in-law keeps
nagging me to have a baby,

264
00:19:48,180 --> 00:19:49,870
but she didn't say anything
about helping my future children.

265
00:19:50,140 --> 00:19:52,140
My mom is far from me either.

266
00:19:52,940 --> 00:19:54,830
You haven't yet work for the company long,

267
00:19:54,830 --> 00:19:56,690
and you can't get in the company kindergarten.
[ A day-care that are located within a very close distance from the office ]

268
00:19:56,690 --> 00:19:58,560
then, there are only two options.

269
00:19:58,560 --> 00:19:59,470
First,

270
00:19:59,470 --> 00:20:01,980
once the birth certificate is completed,
go to nursery for registration...

271
00:20:01,980 --> 00:20:03,700
...and wait for it to be registered
in public kindergartens and private day-cares.

272
00:20:03,700 --> 00:20:06,100
Even so, entering at a public kindergarten
is also like winning a lottery ticket.

273
00:20:06,100 --> 00:20:08,500
Since it's a family system,
and as long as your husband is Korean,

274
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:11,320
being a dual worker family
with many children won't help you at all.

275
00:20:11,810 --> 00:20:12,900
It's like that.

276
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:14,610
What about the second option?

277
00:20:15,270 --> 00:20:16,670
File a divorce.

278
00:20:17,740 --> 00:20:19,070
Pardon? Divorce?

279
00:20:19,670 --> 00:20:22,040
There are even single-parent families in public...

280
00:20:22,040 --> 00:20:23,680
...or company kindergartens, in the first place.

281
00:20:24,160 --> 00:20:25,300
That's unbelievable.

282
00:20:25,540 --> 00:20:27,430
It's not a funny thing.

283
00:20:27,430 --> 00:20:29,670
Single-parent families really have to be like that.

284
00:20:29,850 --> 00:20:33,360
Anyways, I have also lined up in the
company kindergarten for two years.

285
00:20:33,360 --> 00:20:36,430
It's nice to be able to take care
of your children until 9:00 p.m.,

286
00:20:36,430 --> 00:20:38,180
but our superiors have to ask for us every day.

287
00:20:38,180 --> 00:20:39,960
What time does the child has to leave school?

288
00:20:40,340 --> 00:20:44,120
That would just mean you have
to work till 9:00 p.m. all day.

289
00:20:44,120 --> 00:20:46,940
But how good it is to take care of them until 9:00.

290
00:20:46,940 --> 00:20:49,160
Although my son is at the nursery all day long,

291
00:20:49,160 --> 00:20:51,780
I have to let a babysitter take care of him at 7:30.

292
00:20:52,140 --> 00:20:54,250
Goodness. That's what I mean.

293
00:20:54,250 --> 00:20:57,430
At the end, everyone has to seek for their mother's help.

294
00:20:58,100 --> 00:20:59,050
Oh, right.

295
00:20:59,760 --> 00:21:02,570
Don't you think Ms. Han is amazing?

296
00:21:03,070 --> 00:21:04,120
What's wrong?

297
00:21:04,120 --> 00:21:05,430
After going through that kind of thing,

298
00:21:05,430 --> 00:21:06,920
she immediately went to work,

299
00:21:06,920 --> 00:21:08,810
and even works during night shift.

300
00:21:11,140 --> 00:21:12,650
She's very pitiful.

301
00:21:12,900 --> 00:21:15,320
If it's you, do you want to go home?

302
00:21:15,920 --> 00:21:18,770
Besides, Ms. Han had great ambitions for work.

303
00:21:18,770 --> 00:21:21,560
Though she got married early,
she just had a child at a late time.

304
00:21:22,650 --> 00:21:24,030
Well, I guess so.

305
00:21:24,540 --> 00:21:26,050
Oh, by the way.

306
00:21:26,050 --> 00:21:29,940
both you and her entered
the company at the same time, right?

307
00:21:30,210 --> 00:21:31,740
But you actually met again here.

308
00:21:31,740 --> 00:21:33,580
The world is really kind.

309
00:21:33,580 --> 00:21:36,030
If Min-joo has her mother beside her
to help take care of her children,

310
00:21:36,030 --> 00:21:37,810
you could be the on the same length with her.

311
00:21:38,140 --> 00:21:39,120
Me?

312
00:21:39,610 --> 00:21:41,610
Gosh. Forget that.

313
00:21:41,810 --> 00:21:44,180
Even if my mother is still alive,

314
00:21:44,180 --> 00:21:48,050
I don't want her to suffer in exchange for my success.

315
00:21:48,430 --> 00:21:49,670
Isn't it?

316
00:21:49,670 --> 00:21:50,720
She wasn't even at fault.

317
00:21:51,290 --> 00:21:52,500
What fault it could be?

318
00:21:52,500 --> 00:21:53,920
It's the fault of having a daughter.

319
00:22:17,070 --> 00:22:19,850
How is it? Did you like the food?

320
00:22:20,450 --> 00:22:22,650
Yes. I have enjoyed it.

321
00:22:26,360 --> 00:22:27,300
Oh, by the way.

322
00:22:27,540 --> 00:22:30,440
Ms. Lee, I heard you haven't applied
at a company kindergarten.

323
00:22:30,850 --> 00:22:31,850
What to do?

324
00:22:32,030 --> 00:22:34,340
I plan to send him to a private day-care.

325
00:22:34,560 --> 00:22:35,900
This year, at a private-day care...

326
00:22:35,900 --> 00:22:38,920
But you still need someone in the afternoon.

327
00:22:38,920 --> 00:22:42,050
Why not find someone
who can do household chores al day?

328
00:22:42,050 --> 00:22:43,780
Mom, even if she have the money,

329
00:22:43,780 --> 00:22:46,160
Woo-kyung may have to resign and stay at home.

330
00:22:46,540 --> 00:22:48,060
Because of his children,

331
00:22:48,060 --> 00:22:50,060
I can't help it but to take care of them.

332
00:22:51,340 --> 00:22:54,410
By chance, can the mother
help me take care of them?

333
00:22:55,850 --> 00:22:56,650
Pardon?

334
00:22:57,760 --> 00:22:59,580
Well, yes.

335
00:22:59,580 --> 00:23:01,560
Oh dear, I should.

336
00:23:02,450 --> 00:23:04,300
We sincerely thank your family.

337
00:23:04,960 --> 00:23:08,290
As her mother, of course I'm here to help.

338
00:23:09,380 --> 00:23:12,450
But still, they have to save money
before they can buy a house.

339
00:23:12,940 --> 00:23:13,810
By the way.

340
00:23:13,810 --> 00:23:16,930
I heard Woo-kyung's brother is a radio PD.

341
00:23:18,380 --> 00:23:19,160
I am.

342
00:23:19,160 --> 00:23:22,160
Right. What program are you in-charge of?

343
00:23:22,380 --> 00:23:26,470
Well, it's the one that's on-air during 9:00 at night.

344
00:23:26,850 --> 00:23:28,410
I seem to have heard of that.

345
00:23:28,410 --> 00:23:31,500
It seems that he really likes classical music.

346
00:23:31,670 --> 00:23:33,520
Well, of course.

347
00:23:33,960 --> 00:23:36,340
Since childhood, he already liked it.

348
00:23:38,470 --> 00:23:42,600
Can I request for a song next time?

349
00:23:44,230 --> 00:23:46,250
I'm already on leave.

350
00:23:49,340 --> 00:23:50,660
You're on leave?

351
00:23:57,320 --> 00:23:59,380
What are you dissatisfied with?

352
00:23:59,520 --> 00:24:01,760
Because of my children, I have to set a date.

353
00:24:02,180 --> 00:24:03,580
It's just a meeting for today.

354
00:24:03,580 --> 00:24:05,250
It's not even an ordinary meal.

355
00:24:05,850 --> 00:24:09,050
I told you that I might not be able to come today.

356
00:24:09,340 --> 00:24:10,520
And also,

357
00:24:10,520 --> 00:24:13,370
when their family first heard
that Woo-kyung has children,

358
00:24:14,030 --> 00:24:15,850
they didn't made a good expression.

359
00:24:16,210 --> 00:24:17,740
And heard that your dad is a professor...

360
00:24:17,740 --> 00:24:20,320
...and fell in love with me after I became a radio PD.

361
00:24:20,520 --> 00:24:21,700
But...

362
00:24:22,430 --> 00:24:25,960
Why should you say that you're on leave now?

363
00:24:27,320 --> 00:24:28,650
Because it's the truth.

364
00:24:30,010 --> 00:24:31,250
Even so.

365
00:24:31,700 --> 00:24:33,980
Then, you should have resisted for not saying it.

366
00:24:34,760 --> 00:24:37,450
Goodness. It's too embarrasing.

367
00:24:38,560 --> 00:24:39,870
You feel ashamed?

368
00:24:40,920 --> 00:24:42,880
Your daughter held a wedding
just three months after my child's death.

369
00:24:42,880 --> 00:24:44,180
Don't you feel ashamed?

370
00:24:45,650 --> 00:24:46,320
What?

371
00:24:48,250 --> 00:24:50,270
What are you doing? Get in.

372
00:24:51,940 --> 00:24:55,650
You think this is about getting married now?

373
00:24:56,500 --> 00:24:58,570
What should I do if they have children, then?

374
00:24:58,570 --> 00:25:01,610
Our in-laws said that they have
to work hard before they grow big.

375
00:25:01,760 --> 00:25:03,230
What's wrong with you?

376
00:25:03,430 --> 00:25:05,570
How come you don't understand what I've felt?

377
00:25:06,780 --> 00:25:08,410
Then, do you understand what I've felt?

378
00:25:09,850 --> 00:25:11,920
Or else, why don't you tie it up and compare it?

379
00:25:11,920 --> 00:25:14,160
Who's someone's heart
do you think have gone rotten!?

380
00:25:19,050 --> 00:25:21,520
I mean, why are you losing your temper on me?

381
00:25:21,850 --> 00:25:23,410
Is that because of me?

382
00:25:32,580 --> 00:25:33,670
Where are you going?

383
00:25:33,900 --> 00:25:35,430
Get on the car.

384
00:25:37,780 --> 00:25:39,780
Just go first. I'll follow you soon.

385
00:26:41,650 --> 00:26:45,040
<i>That's why, I told you to just stay at home
until Yoo-na starts to go to school.</i>

386
00:26:46,300 --> 00:26:49,540
<i>I have begged you to just stay at home.</i>

387
00:26:51,030 --> 00:26:53,520
<i>Are you still a mother in this way!?</i>

388
00:27:00,420 --> 00:27:02,010
<i>What to do?</i>

389
00:27:05,520 --> 00:27:07,120
<i>What should we do?</i>

390
00:28:07,100 --> 00:28:08,210
You see, Ma'am.

391
00:28:12,670 --> 00:28:15,870
I'm not sure how to say this to you.

392
00:28:17,870 --> 00:28:19,610
I'm really sorry for that day.

393
00:28:20,900 --> 00:28:23,560
Because of me, they have to held a company dinner.

394
00:28:29,450 --> 00:28:30,630
So-hee.

395
00:28:33,410 --> 00:28:35,680
I hope you will not say anything about that anymore.

396
00:28:46,940 --> 00:28:48,670
<i>The elevator is going down.</i>

397
00:28:58,760 --> 00:29:00,580
<i>The door is about to close.</i>

398
00:29:15,700 --> 00:29:17,760
<i>I watched over the house and left.</i>

399
00:29:17,760 --> 00:29:19,760
<i>It's very neat and I liked the place.</i>

400
00:29:19,760 --> 00:29:21,980
<i>I'm reconsidering it at the moment.</i>

401
00:29:22,500 --> 00:29:24,700
<i>I can adjust the selling price.</i>

402
00:29:25,030 --> 00:29:27,140
<i>Help me sell it as soon as possible.</i>

403
00:29:30,010 --> 00:29:32,380
Damn you! Why are you blocking my way?

404
00:29:36,850 --> 00:29:39,120
Damn it! What the hell is this?

405
00:29:44,670 --> 00:29:46,030
Damn it!

406
00:29:51,380 --> 00:29:52,960
What a nuisance!

407
00:29:53,320 --> 00:29:55,450
Goodness! What a nuisance!

408
00:29:55,960 --> 00:29:58,900
Hey, are you ignoring me now!?

409
00:29:59,050 --> 00:30:02,260
- Are you ignoring me, huh?
- Please just leave!

410
00:30:03,830 --> 00:30:07,180
How dare the two of you team up together!?

411
00:30:08,180 --> 00:30:09,760
Damn you!

412
00:30:21,640 --> 00:30:26,650
[ Police ]

413
00:30:26,740 --> 00:30:28,960
Thank you so much.

414
00:30:30,160 --> 00:30:31,080
You see,

415
00:30:31,360 --> 00:30:33,850
I thank you for what you did before, so...

416
00:30:34,450 --> 00:30:36,520
No need. It's just fine.

417
00:30:40,960 --> 00:30:43,360
Please just bring this with you.

418
00:30:45,160 --> 00:30:46,500
Thank you.

419
00:30:47,410 --> 00:30:48,610
Thank you.

420
00:31:33,200 --> 00:31:37,840
[ Yoo-na's dad ]

421
00:31:39,360 --> 00:31:40,340
<i>Hello.</i>

422
00:31:42,450 --> 00:31:43,270
Jung-eun.

423
00:31:43,580 --> 00:31:44,410
Yes.

424
00:31:45,700 --> 00:31:46,630
Why?

425
00:31:47,900 --> 00:31:49,250
<i>You're off from work?</i>

426
00:31:50,900 --> 00:31:51,720
I am.

427
00:31:52,220 --> 00:31:55,560
<i>Next week, my sister will give birth.</i>

428
00:31:56,360 --> 00:31:57,920
<i>Let's go together this Sunday.</i>

429
00:32:01,470 --> 00:32:02,340
<i>Jung-eun.</i>

430
00:32:04,100 --> 00:32:05,610
Just go by yourself.

431
00:33:28,500 --> 00:33:30,860
<i>We want to have a home full of children.</i>

432
00:33:47,500 --> 00:33:48,430
<i>Jung-eun.</i>

433
00:33:56,180 --> 00:33:57,630
<i>I guess it's a daughter.</i>

434
00:35:25,120 --> 00:35:26,650
Yoo-na.

435
00:35:29,610 --> 00:35:30,740
Mom...

436
00:35:32,810 --> 00:35:41,420
I should have hold this tight and hug you.

437
00:35:42,380 --> 00:35:44,830
I was wrong.

438
00:35:45,450 --> 00:35:47,540
It's all my fault.

439
00:35:49,830 --> 00:35:52,160
I'm really sorry, my child.

440
00:35:53,580 --> 00:35:55,980
I'm really sorry, Yoo-na!

441
00:35:58,450 --> 00:36:00,120
Yoo-na!

442
00:36:36,760 --> 00:36:38,230
It's really strange.

443
00:36:38,630 --> 00:36:41,050
We get stuck from the traffic jam every day.

444
00:36:43,780 --> 00:36:44,900
Every day?

445
00:36:46,610 --> 00:36:47,430
What?

446
00:36:49,340 --> 00:36:51,120
Do you often come this way?

447
00:36:52,380 --> 00:36:54,270
Ever since Mom came to Seoul,

448
00:36:54,270 --> 00:36:56,230
I've never went to her house.

449
00:36:59,380 --> 00:37:01,870
I've been there a few times to see her recently.

450
00:37:06,180 --> 00:37:09,250
And also... This one.

451
00:37:13,760 --> 00:37:15,450
I didn't want to give it to you.

452
00:37:17,050 --> 00:37:18,720
But you two are very close,

453
00:37:19,720 --> 00:37:20,830
so I'm giving it to you.

454
00:37:26,940 --> 00:37:28,580
Woo-kyung is pregnant.

455
00:37:38,300 --> 00:37:40,230
Please convey my sincere wishes to her.

456
00:37:42,050 --> 00:37:43,300
How months is her baby?

457
00:37:43,720 --> 00:37:44,980
3 months or so.

458
00:37:47,360 --> 00:37:51,430
It should have been the time when Yoo-na left us.

459
00:37:57,740 --> 00:37:59,760
Call Mom and tell her...

460
00:37:59,760 --> 00:38:01,500
...we'll be there 30 minutes later.

461
00:38:08,120 --> 00:38:09,540
You just call her.

462
00:38:09,810 --> 00:38:11,780
I'm driving the car right now.

463
00:38:15,980 --> 00:38:20,500
<i>Dear user, the number you have dialed does not exist.</i>

464
00:38:20,500 --> 00:38:22,010
<i>Please confirm and call again.</i>

465
00:38:22,010 --> 00:38:23,250
Oh, right.

466
00:38:23,520 --> 00:38:25,230
She changed her phone number.

467
00:38:25,580 --> 00:38:26,630
Why?

468
00:38:27,180 --> 00:38:28,270
When?

469
00:38:29,520 --> 00:38:32,920
Well, she may have lost her phone.

470
00:38:33,830 --> 00:38:35,100
Use my phone.

471
00:38:39,720 --> 00:38:41,250
Let's just go.

472
00:39:06,940 --> 00:39:08,030
Why aren't you getting out?

473
00:39:10,520 --> 00:39:12,030
I just don't want to go outside.

474
00:39:13,250 --> 00:39:15,250
I'm tired of listening to others' comfort.

475
00:39:17,720 --> 00:39:18,900
Just go and come back.

476
00:39:19,450 --> 00:39:20,980
I'll just stay here.

477
00:39:24,320 --> 00:39:25,160
Okay.

478
00:39:53,650 --> 00:39:56,520
Mother-in law, this is me. Woo-cheol.

479
00:40:13,780 --> 00:40:15,560
Mother-in-law, you're inside, right?

480
00:40:17,340 --> 00:40:19,830
I've called you many times that I'll come here.

481
00:40:19,830 --> 00:40:21,230
Have you forgotten it?

482
00:40:22,450 --> 00:40:24,070
Well, yes.

483
00:40:24,720 --> 00:40:26,830
Mother-in-law, haven't you eaten yet, right?

484
00:40:28,430 --> 00:40:29,940
Then, please get ready and come out.

485
00:40:29,940 --> 00:40:31,250
We'll be waiting here outside.

486
00:40:32,340 --> 00:40:34,960
Well, mother-in-law.
Jung-eun is also joining with us.

487
00:40:37,210 --> 00:40:38,430
Please hurry up and come out.

488
00:40:49,900 --> 00:40:51,780
Did she forgot about today's appointment?

489
00:40:52,560 --> 00:40:53,850
She'll come out soon.

490
00:41:49,410 --> 00:41:52,540
Mother-in-law, eat this. It's already cooked.

491
00:41:56,940 --> 00:41:58,430
Want me to grill some garlic?

492
00:41:58,610 --> 00:42:00,940
Don't you like eating garlic, right?

493
00:42:01,270 --> 00:42:03,610
Oh my, aren't you Choi Soon-ok?

494
00:42:04,560 --> 00:42:06,760
I'm Mi-sook, you know.

495
00:42:06,760 --> 00:42:10,140
I opened a store at the central market
but you have moved.

496
00:42:10,140 --> 00:42:11,690
You don't remember it?

497
00:42:11,940 --> 00:42:14,180
My mom goes in the same church with you.

498
00:42:14,180 --> 00:42:15,760
You're the one who persuaded her.

499
00:42:16,270 --> 00:42:17,850
You have come to Seoul for a while?

500
00:42:18,160 --> 00:42:20,560
My family also came here.

501
00:42:21,410 --> 00:42:22,850
I see.

502
00:42:22,850 --> 00:42:25,180
So this is your daughter and son-in-law.

503
00:42:25,210 --> 00:42:27,120
- Oh, yes. Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

504
00:42:27,160 --> 00:42:29,070
Gosh. I'm envious of you.

505
00:42:29,070 --> 00:42:31,610
My sister also works at a company in Seoul,

506
00:42:31,610 --> 00:42:35,050
but she couldn't come to my mother's shop,
so my nephew came instead.

507
00:42:35,520 --> 00:42:37,830
Huh? But what about the child?

508
00:42:38,670 --> 00:42:40,700
You didn't bring her with you?

509
00:42:44,300 --> 00:42:47,500
Oh my. Where did my senses go?
Please wait a second.

510
00:42:48,360 --> 00:42:51,010
Mom! Choi Soon-ok is here.

511
00:42:51,160 --> 00:42:54,430
She was the one who opened
a fruit stand and went to Seoul.

512
00:42:55,050 --> 00:42:55,870
Huh?

